Business Brief -- Riggs National Corp.:
   Net Income of $2.1 Million
   Posted for Fourth Quarter
For the full year, Riggs reported a wider loss of $63.5
million, compared with a loss of $56.6 million in 1990. It
took a $49.8 million provision for losses on accelerated
disposition of real estate assets, although the loan-loss
provision narrowed to $43.5 million from $105.5 million. Net
interest income fell 10% to $156 million.
   Riggs, with $5.53 billion in assets, is attempting to
raise $25 million to $50 million in much-needed capital
through a rights offering to stockholders. Shares rose 25
cents apiece to $5.375 in national over-the-counter trading.